-- Athens Street Fixtures Damage Exceeded 1 Million Euros, ANA Says
-- B y   T o m   S t o u k a s
-- 2012-02-14T11:54:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-14/athens-street-fixtures-damage-exceeded-1-million-euros-ana-says.html
Rioting in  Athens  against austerity
measures passed by the Greek parliament on Feb. 12 caused more
than 1 million euros ($1.3 million) of damage to street
fixtures, Athens News Agency reported, citing  Andreas Varelis ,
the deputy mayor for sanitation  Damage included smashed sidewalks, railings, traffic lights
and street lights, the state-run news agency said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tom Stoukas in Athens at 
 astoukas@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
